t chaps his butt.  /hug mine.  Actually, my resists are comparable to Veleals, and he has more mana and about 300 more HP..  I don't care about HP too much as I have 200 doses of 300 pt heals that cast instantly (albeit expensively) .  I don't argue he has nice things, I argue that his perspective is not only insanely biased (IE The view is great from the top, so it must be equally as impressive as the valley ), but that he is claiming things about combat that is simply not true.<br>
<br>
I also have all focus IV things, and while I am not saying we are completely worthless, I am saying that a level 60 char with very few aa can give me a run for my money that is disproportionate to the amount of effort/gear they have acquired.  You may be right, Brillin, that the gap in his gear v.s. the gap in his foes hear is far greater then what we face on VZ.  Although, it should be noted that a marginally equipped healer, or a Melee with a formidable 2HB can pretty much kick anyones ass (including Veleal) indoors.  I am stating that Verant has worsened this situation, and DO have the capability to correct this, as they have broken it.  <br>
<br>
I don't want a DT every 2 hours 44 min.  I want a even palying field where effort = effectiveness.  Right now, it is far from that, and PvP skills have very little to do with the outcome in certain scenarios.  This simply should not be the case.  This isn't &quot;whining&quot;, this is about having a sense of fairness.  There are alot of easily correctable things that could be done right now:<br>
<br>
water dancing:  Lame, and really serves no purpose in PvP then to allow rangers to shoot you while being immune to spells, or to allow other classes to heal/med at will.  We don't receive the same benifit.<br>
<br>
Healing classes:  I still know for a fact that even the best equipped Wizard is garbage against a good healer.<br>
<br>
7-8 K HP characters:  I have yet to see a wizard survive the damage incured while trying to crank out this type of damage, esp indoors.<br>
<br>
