Anyways, if you believe that pvp is defined by the bazaar, well - I almost understand you stating we suck as a pvp class. Only bards are more mobility dependent in pvp than wizards are, it's the class strengths. Small enclosed areas with no terain are the worst place you could pick .. half of being good in pvp is knowing when and where to fight, and when and where not to (though I've killed plenty of retards in the bazaar). <br>
<br>
PvP is two parts - in every game it's in. <br>
<br>
#1 - Killing people - doing enough damage, and doing it before they can get away.<br>
<br>
#2 - Not dying to other people - being able to absorb or avoid damage, and being able to disengage when you know you are losing<br>
<br>
Wizards in EQ excell at both those. For example, look at the only PvP server that keeps score.<br>
